Other leaders of the G7 are set to clash with Trump when they pressure him to lift sanctions on steel and aluminium they fear could lead to a trade war. WASHINGTON - US President Donald Trump said on Friday Russia should be attending a Group of Seven nations meeting, as he prepared to fly to Canada to attend part of the three-day conference. Other leaders of the G7 are set to clash with Trump when they pressure him to lift sanctions on steel and aluminium they fear could lead to a trade war. Trump is scheduled to leave early on Saturday for Singapore to prepare for a summit with North Korean leader Kim Jong Un on Tuesday.